hwChanbIsdnTable.name: hwChanbIsdnTable
hwChanbIsdnTable.description: This table is used to describe the router's B Channels infomation

hwChanbIsdnIf.name: hwChanbIsdnIf
hwChanbIsdnIf.description: this object is used to describe the virtual interface value associated with one neighbor.

hwChanbIsdnPermit.name: hwChanbIsdnPermit
hwChanbIsdnPermit.description: this object is used to describe the call permissions.

hwChanbIsdnAddr.name: hwChanbIsdnAddr
hwChanbIsdnAddr.description: this object is used to descirbe the call address by which we call one nieghbor.

hwChanbIsdnCallerAddr.name: hwChanbIsdnCallerAddr
hwChanbIsdnCallerAddr.description: this object is used to describe the callser address which will be known by B channels.

hwChanbIsdnCallType.name: hwChanbIsdnCallType
hwChanbIsdnCallType.description: this object is used to describe that whether it is an incoming call or an outging call.

hwChanbIsdnInfoType.name: hwChanbIsdnInfoType
hwChanbIsdnInfoType.description: this object is used to describe the information type on the call

hwChanbIsdnState.name: hwChanbIsdnState
hwChanbIsdnState.description: this object is used to manage the call by NMS

hwChanbIsdnCallFreeReason.name: hwChanbIsdnCallFreeReason
hwChanbIsdnCallFreeReason.description: this object is used to describe the reason why last call is cleard

hwChanbIsdnCallFreeCode.name: hwChanbIsdnCallFreeCode
hwChanbIsdnCallFreeCode.description: this object is used to describe the reason code for the last call down.

hwChanbIsdnCallAccept.name: hwChanbIsdnCallAccept
hwChanbIsdnCallAccept.description: this object is used to describe the accepted call number from the B channels

hwChanbIsdnCallReject.name: hwChanbIsdnCallReject
hwChanbIsdnCallReject.description: this object is used to describe the refused call number from B channels .

hwChanbIsdnCallSuccess.name: hwChanbIsdnCallSuccess
hwChanbIsdnCallSuccess.description: this object is used to describe the successful call number to B channels after system restart.

hwChanbIsdnCallFailure.name: hwChanbIsdnCallFailure
hwChanbIsdnCallFailure.description: this object is used to describe the failing call number to B channels after system restart

hwChanbIsdnMaxKeepTime.name: hwChanbIsdnMaxKeepTime
hwChanbIsdnMaxKeepTime.description: This object is used to descirbe the maximum duration time in milliseconds.

hwChanbIsdnLastKeepTime.name: hwChanbIsdnLastKeepTime
hwChanbIsdnLastKeepTime.description: this object is used to describe the last call duration time in milliseconds

hwChanbIsdnLastCallTime.name: hwChanbIsdnLastCallTime
hwChanbIsdnLastCallTime.description: this object is used to describe the sysUpTime after last call attempt was made.

hwChanbTrapEnable.name: hwChanbTrapEnable
hwChanbTrapEnable.description: This object is used to control sending trap

hwQ931CallSetupTrapEnable.name: hwQ931CallSetupTrapEnable
hwQ931CallSetupTrapEnable.description: This object is used to control sending callsetup trap.

hwQ931CallClearTrapEnable.name: hwQ931CallClearTrapEnable
hwQ931CallClearTrapEnable.description: This object is used to control sending callclear trap

hwQ931IsdnTable.name: hwQ931IsdnTable
hwQ931IsdnTable.description: This table describes B channel information for the use of Q931

hwQ931IsdnEntry.name: hwQ931IsdnEntry
hwQ931IsdnEntry.description: A B channel entry in the Q931.

hwQ931IsdnOpIndex.name: hwQ931IsdnOpIndex
hwQ931IsdnOpIndex.description: Index of the B ISDN channel interface managed by Q93

hwQ931IsdnLastCalled.name: hwQ931IsdnLastCalled
hwQ931IsdnLastCalled.description: This object describes the called ISDN number. When an outgoing call is established successfully, the value of this node is the call number of this device, otherwise the value is null string

hwQ931IsdnLastCalling.name: hwQ931IsdnLastCalling
hwQ931IsdnLastCalling.description: This object describes the calling ISDN number. When an incoming call is established successfully, the value of this node is the call number of peer device, otherwise the value is null string.

hwQ931IsdnLastCauseDisc.name: hwQ931IsdnLastCauseDisc
hwQ931IsdnLastCauseDisc.description: This object describes last cause of disconnection. In hwQ931IsdnCallClear trap, the value of this node is the reason of disconnection, this node is only valid for hwQ931IsdnCallClear trap, the value of this node is unknown in other situation. unknown: unknown error. normCallClr: normal call clearing. noRouteToTransNet: no route to specified transit network. noRouteToDest: no route to destination. switchEquCongest: switching equipment congestion. netOutofOrder: network out of order.

hwQ931IsdnCallDirection.name: hwQ931IsdnCallDirection
hwQ931IsdnCallDirection.description: This object describes the direction of the current call.

hwQ931IsdnCallTimeOpen.name: hwQ931IsdnCallTimeOpen
hwQ931IsdnCallTimeOpen.description: This object describes the start time of this call. start time is the time of an existent call that has just been established.

hwQ931IsdnCallTimeClose.name: hwQ931IsdnCallTimeClose
hwQ931IsdnCallTimeClose.description: This object describes the close time of this call. This node is only vaild for hwQ931IsdnCallClear trap. In other situation the value of this node is zero. In hwQ931IsdnCallClear trap, this node provides the time of an existent call that the call has just been cleared.

hwLapdIsdnTable.name: hwLapdIsdnTable
hwLapdIsdnTable.description: This table is used to describe the config of ISDN D channel.

hwLapdIsdnIf.name: hwLapdIsdnIf
hwLapdIsdnIf.description: This object is used to describe the D channel interface value associated with one neighbor.

hwLapdIsdnProtocol.name: hwLapdIsdnProtocol
hwLapdIsdnProtocol.description: This object is used to describe the protocol D channel applied. For E1, the protocol may be dss1, qsig, etsi. For T1, the protocol may be ess5, ansi, att, dss1, etsi, ni2, ntt, qsig. For BRI, the protocol may be ansi, dss1, etsi, ni, ntt.

hwLapdIsdnIfMode.name: hwLapdIsdnIfMode
hwLapdIsdnIfMode.description: The physical interface mode. For TE mode, the value of this object is userSide. For NT mode, the value of this object is networkSide.

hwLapdIsdnLinkStatus.name: hwLapdIsdnLinkStatus
hwLapdIsdnLinkStatus.description: The operational status of this interface: inactive all layers are inactive. l1Active layer 1 is activated, layer 2 datalink not established. l2Active layer 1 is activated, layer 2 datalink established.

hwLapdStatusTrapEnable.name: hwLapdStatusTrapEnable
hwLapdStatusTrapEnable.description: This object is used to control sending hwLapdIsdnStatusChange trap.

hwChanbIsdnCall.name: hwChanbIsdnCall
hwChanbIsdnCall.description: When one call is setup ,cleard or determined , the trap is sent to NMS

hwQ931IsdnCallSetup.name: hwQ931IsdnCallSetup
hwQ931IsdnCallSetup.description: This trap/inform is sent to the manager whenever a call is established successfully.

hwQ931IsdnCallClear.name: hwQ931IsdnCallClear
hwQ931IsdnCallClear.description: This trap/inform is sent to the manager under the following conditions: - an existent call is normally cleared. - an existent call is determined to have ultimately failed, and has been cleared. - the existent call is cleared when the BRI/PRI port is down. - the existent call is cleared when the dialer rule is down.

hwLapdIsdnStatusChange.name: hwLapdIsdnStatusChange
hwLapdIsdnStatusChange.description: This trap/inform is sent to the manager whenever the D-channel of an interface changes state.
